157350777.review:
Fairly unique and enjoyable open world spin-off set in a very rarely used in gaming setting. In my opinion it is a very underrated game with a compelling exploration and it can be very engrossing at times. Obviously it's not without problems and limitations set by time period, so if you think you're gonna 360 noscope some pore caveman with Barrett 50 cal you're gonna be disappointed, but if you like classic Far Cry gameplay loop and don't mind repetition check it out.

Pros:
- Very immersive world;
- Cool invented language and voice acting;
- Good attention to detail;
- Great sense of progression;
- Enemy variety;
- Fun exploration;
- Survival mode;
- Good stealth;
- Cool taming system;
- Amazing visuals;
- Great optimization;
- Good controls;
- Memorable characters;
- Great sound system and soundtrack;

Cons:
- Ubisoft Connect(Upaly) is complete garbage;
- Too eventful at times;
- Like almost all games in this series, gets very repetitive;
- Mediocre melee system;

